Sentencas: While there have been significant breakthroughs in new functional cathodes facilitating the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs), sluggish oxygen charge transfer across the cathode/electrolyte heterogeneous interface also hinders overall performance.
Titulo: Evolution of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells via Fast Interfacial Oxygen Crossover

Sentencas: To promote oxygen ion exchange at the interface, a thin layer of cerium oxide decorated by an amorphous cobalt oxide overcoating was introduced to function as a fast oxygen ion transport pathway at the interface.
Titulo: Evolution of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells via Fast Interfacial Oxygen Crossover

Sentencas: The peak power density (PPD) of the modified cell achieved 767 mW/cm(2) at a low operation temperature of 550 degrees C, which is almost 3 times the power output of the unmodified cell.
Titulo: Evolution of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells via Fast Interfacial Oxygen Crossover

Sentencas: Oxygen isotope exchange confirmed that the oxygen reduction active cobalt oxide nanolayer drastically reduced the energy barrier for oxygen transport across the solid-solid interface.
Titulo: Evolution of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells via Fast Interfacial Oxygen Crossover

Sentencas: Such interface modification successfully demonstrates an effective route to enable fast ORR and oxygen transport across the cathode/electrolyte interface at low temperature.
Titulo: Evolution of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells via Fast Interfacial Oxygen Crossover
